</copyright><lastBuildDate>Sun, 06 May 2018 11:48:18 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>Nikola (getnikola.com)</generator><docs>http://blogs.law.harvard.edu/tech/rss</docs><item><title>Playing with PELAGIOS: Arachne was easy after nomisma</title><link>https://paregorios.org/posts/2012/02/playing-with-pelagios-arachne-was-easy/</link><dc:creator>Tom Elliott</dc:creator><description>&lt;p&gt;Querying &lt;a href="http://pleiades.stoa.org/"&gt;Pleiades&lt;/a&gt; annotations out of &lt;a href="http://arachne.uni-koeln.de/drupal/node/235#arachnePelagiosCooperation"&gt;Arachne RDF&lt;/a&gt; was as simple as loading the Arachne Objects by Places RDF file into 4store &lt;a href="http://horothesia.blogspot.com/2012/02/playing-with-pelagios-nomisma.html"&gt;the same way I did nomisma and running the same SPARQL query&lt;/a&gt;.  Cost: 5 minutes. Now I know about 29 objects in the Arachne database that they think are related to &lt;a href="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462086/"&gt;Akragas/Agrigentum&lt;/a&gt;. For example:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;41149: Sarkophag mit dem Hippolytosmythos (Agrigent, S. Nicola):         &lt;div class="p1"&gt;&lt;a href="http://arachne.uni-koeln.de/entity/1098273"&gt;http://arachne.uni-koeln.de/entity/1098273&lt;/a&gt; == &lt;a href="http://arachne.uni-koeln.de/item/objekt/41149"&gt;http://arachne.uni-koeln.de/item/objekt/41149&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;75: Statue des Apollon (Agrigent, Museo Civico): &lt;a href="http://arachne.uni-koeln.de/entity/1060434"&gt;http://arachne.uni-koeln.de/entity/1060434&lt;/a&gt; == &lt;a href="http://arachne.uni-koeln.de/item/objekt/75"&gt;http://arachne.uni-koeln.de/item/objekt/75&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;75000: Atlant des Olympieions von Agrigent (Akragas, Agrigentum, Agrigento): &lt;a href="http://arachne.uni-koeln.de/entity/1111253"&gt;http://arachne.uni-koeln.de/entity/1111253&lt;/a&gt; == &lt;a href="http://arachne.uni-koeln.de/item/objekt/75000"&gt;http://arachne.uni-koeln.de/item/objekt/75000&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;</description><category>arachne</category><category>horothesia</category><category>linkeddata</category><category>LOD</category><category>nomisma</category><category>pelagios</category><category>pelagiosplay</category><category>pleiades</category><category>rdf</category><category>sparql</category><guid>https://paregorios.org/posts/2012/02/playing-with-pelagios-arachne-was-easy/</guid><pubDate>Thu, 02 Feb 2012 05:18:00 GMT</pubDate></item></channel></rss>